This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it focuses on improving the performance and accuracy of lightweight networks in the ImageNet dataset. Additionally, the proposed model involves the use of convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of novel techniques to enhance information interaction in neural networks, which could fall under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

Furthermore, the proposed Exchange Shortcut Connection and Attention based Hierarchical Joint Decision involve the use of deep learning techniques, which could fall under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of language processing techniques to describe the proposed model and experiments, which could fall under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) category.
